cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SI 

The paper presents a breast tumor recognition framework based on microarray gene expression data. The proposed method involves wrapper gene selection, feature selection using a modified NMF model, and inverse projection sparse representation for classification. These techniques are commonly used in machine learning and data mining, which fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses optimization using generalized ADMM, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Therefore, the likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, and cs.SI.
